title: Boys Soccer Roundup: Mansfield Christian wins
text:
Boys Soccer Roundup: Mansfield Christian wins Staff report 10:51 p.m. EDT September 29, 2015 STK Stock 1 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Mansfield Christian 7, Kidron Central Christian 1 
The Flames (11-0-1) defeated Central Christian on Tuesday evening. Brandon Mount led the team with five goals followed by Jared McPeek with two. Sam Paul had three assists and Mount and Corbin Thebeault each had one assist. J.P. Tureblood had five saves in goal. Mansfield Christian are the Mid-Buckeye Conference Champions. 
Ontario 4, Willard 1 
Logan Osborne scored two goals and Jake Hairston and Ty Carcione each had a goal Tuesday night for host Ontario (7-4-1, 5-1) in a Northern Ohio League win. Osborne and Erik Kilmczynski each had an assist. Noah Brokaw had five saves for the Warriors. Sergio Lopez scored for Willard. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1KK0GAH More Stories
